Work with basic texts of art history. The founding purpose of mainly seminar-style approach is to learn preconditions and opportunities of art history as its own discipline from Plato's academy to Modernism.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Give an overview of development of art history on the general background of the era's aesthetic and philosophical thought from Antiquity to Modernism. The purpose of the course is to study prerequisites of art history as its own train of thought and discipline of science, and their usage as main cornerstone of art history.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The attested student has a theoretical base for acquiring the profession and prerequisites to treat art historical events.
